 <p>Bard of 54 songs<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=193338">Hraka Frithrah <IMG SRC="http://www.users.drew.edu/jleto/endless/destruction.jpg" ALT="I'm Destruction!" BORDER="0"><BR><font face="courier new" size="2"><a href="http://www.users.drew.edu/jleto/endless/">Which Member of the Endless Are <i>You</i>?</a></font></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000080><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/uravilicuslolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravilicus LoLF</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#70DB93>(6/14/02 5:13:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=99.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Multiple mob pulling strategy</span><hr size=1> Just to clarify a bit more -<br>
<br>
The idea is that this technique is only used in a place where pulling can be completely controlled.  I used Umbral as an example simply because no mobs ever wander to the ME zone where the raid party would be doing the killing, therefore there is no need to worry about wanderers.  The same could be done in PoG, etc. because there is so much space the AE spells won't grab any unwanted adds that aren't intentionally pulled to the group.<br>
<br>
The idea is simple, crowd control is only necessary in that there is one tank (minimum) per mob pulled.  We are then able to kill TWICE as many mobs in the same amount of time as we normally kill a single.  Clerics save mana, casters save mana, and it further prepares us for other encounters that REQUIRE multi-tanking.  Let's face it, if we don't get very proficient at multiple tank strategies we won't be ready for the high end encounters where we will go through 3 main tanks before one is stabilized on the mob with a CH rotation, or the ring quests where there are constant adds that need to be tanked as opposed to mezzed.<br>
<br>
The benefits are many - Greater mana efficiency, greater tanking skills for ALL of our tanks, increased ability to tackle situations where splits are NECESSARY, and overall better communication and raid organization.<br>
<br>
There is no doubt that this, like ANY strategy worth anything requires work...but this strategy certainly would be very effective in MANY circumstances, while the single pull strategy everyone is familiar with is simply effective in MOST circumstances, but not ALL circumstances.<br>
<br>
P.S. Enchanter AE stun spells can be chain cast and really use VERY little mana to cast.  This technique is also possible without as much concern for having one-tank-per-mob when the mobs are all stunnable, but this isn't the idea I had in mind, this is your typical AE group + some melee thrown in...the idea behind the strategy above is to control pulling, control mob placement, and controll aggro management.  When this is done successfully, overall raid effectiveness is amplified tremendously because casters then can incorporate AE spells and supporting melee classes (rogue/etc) can rotate their attacks on different mobs to avoid aggro. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000060><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ucloudsoul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cloudsoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#70DB93>(6/14/02 7:45:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=99.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Multiple mob pulling strategy</span><hr size=1> Anyone with experience of an aoe group knows how good this can be, chanters can recycle their 3 colour stuns to amazing effect so that mobs hardly get to move and necros with Vitae and mind wrack can also be extremely useful.<br>
<br>
But while umbral would be a good testing ground surely this can't be the end aim of a new type of fed raid, if I'm risking death I want the rewards to outweigh the danger and a moktor bracer just doesn't cut it.<br>
<br>
I think the whole purpose for this kind of fighting is in a zone where we know adds can't be controlled and we either try something new and inventive or can't do the zone.<br>
<br>
If we can pull it the normal way why get complicated, zones like CT and Chardok are where we need to get einsteinish.<br>
